al links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=1501374|name=Adam Rayner}}\n* [http://www.saint.org/actor-adam-rayner.htm Adam Rayner] at The Saint Club's official website\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rayner, Adam}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:Actors from Shropshire]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:English emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actors from Shrewsbury]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Durham University]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Adam Rayner\n| birth_name = Adam Chance Angus Rayner\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1977|8|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Shrewsbury]], [[Shropshire]], England\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 2001\u2013present\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Lucy Brown]]|2015}}\n| children = 2\n}}\n\n'''Adam Chance Angus Rayner''' (born 28 August 1977) is an English actor, who has appeared on television in ''[[Mistresses (UK TV series)|Mistresses]]'', ''[[At Home with the Braithwaites]]'' and ''[[Making Waves (TV series)|Making Waves]]''. He has also appeared on stage in ''[[The Rivals]]'' ([[Bristol Old Vic]], 2004), ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' ([[Royal Shakespeare Theatre]], 2006) and ''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]'' ([[Novello Theatre|Novello]], 2006).\n\nRayner studied at [[Durham University]] and after graduating completed a two-year acting course at [[LAMDA]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adam Rayner |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1501374/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm |website=IMDb |accessdate=29 January 2020}}{{unreliable source|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n\nHe made an appearance as 'Dr. Gail' in the 2010 Christmas Special 'The Perfect Christmas' episode of the award winning [[BBC]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]'' alongside [[Sally Phillips]], [[Miranda Hart]], [[Tom Ellis (actor)|Tom Ellis]], [[Sarah Hadland]] and [[Patricia Hodge]], and his character returned in the fourth episode of the third series, titled \"Je Regret Nothing\".<ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01q03nv |title = Dr Gail returns to Series 3}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2012, it was announced that Rayner was cast as [[Simon Templar]] in a pilot for a new television series based on the character.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.deadline.com/2012/12/eliza-dushku-to-co-star-in-the-saint-backdoor-pilot-roger-moore-to-co-produce/|title= Eliza Dushku To Co-Star In \u2018The Saint\u2019 Backdoor Pilot, Roger Moore To Co-Produce|first= Nellie|last= Andreeva|work= [[Deadline Hollywood]]|date= 2012-12-10|accessdate= 2012-12-17}}</ref> Principal photography began on Monday, 17 December 2012 in Pacific Palisades, California.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://blog.saint.org/2012/12/the-first-week-on-set-of-thesaint.html|title= Week One on the Set of The Saint|work=The Saint News|date= 2012-12-20|accessdate= 2012-12-31}}</ref>  Executive producer [[Roger Moore]] was unable to sell the pilot, and Rayner was cast as the lead in the [[FX (TV channel)|FX]] television series, ''[[Tyrant (TV series)|Tyrant]]'', which ran from June 2014 to September 2016.\n\nRayner's mother is American and father is English and also holds a [[dual citizenship]] for the United Kingdom and the United States. He married actress [[Lucy Brown]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/146845/a-palace-built-on-strawberry-fields|title=A palace built on strawberry fields|author=Ruben V. Nepales|work=inquirer.net}}</ref> on New Year's Eve 2015. They have a son together, Jack, born 28 December 2014, and a daughter, Annie Rose, born 11 July 2017.<ref>http://instagram.com/p/xNZKnSpvc8/?modal=true</ref> <ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BlHvpLmnHi6/</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''{{sortname|The|Goodbye Plane|nolink=1}}''\n| Leonard aged 20\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''{{sortname|The|Rivals|nolink=1}}''\n| Captain Jack Absolute\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''RedMeansGo''\n| Sam\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Love and Other Disasters]]''\n| Tom / Fantasy David\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Straightheads]]''\n| Jago\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Steel Trap]]''\n| Adam\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''{{sortname|The|Task|dab=film}}''\n| Taylor\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Tracers (film)|Tracers]]''\n| Miller\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[At Home with the Braithwaites]]''\n| Nick Bottomley\n| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Making Waves (TV series)|Making Waves]]''\n| Lt. Sam Quartermaine\n| Episode: \"Episode 2\"\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Vincent (TV series)|Vincent]]''\n| James O'Connor\n| Episode: \"The Prodigal Son\"\n|-\n| 2005, 2007\n| ''[[Sensitive Skin (UK TV series)|Sensitive Skin]]''\n| Greg\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''{{sortname|The|Line of Beauty|dab=miniseries}}''\n| Ricky\n| Miniseries; episode: \"To Whom Do You Beautifully Belong\"\n|-\n| 2008\u20132010\n| ''[[Mistresses (UK TV series)|Mistresses]]''\n| Dominic Montgomery\n| Main role; 16 episodes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Doctor Who]]''\n| Roger Curbishley\n| Episode: \"[[The Unicorn and the Wasp]]\"\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Abroad''\n| Edward Walpole\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[Hawthorne (TV series)|Hawthorne]]''\n| Dr. Steve Shaw\n| Main role (seasons 2\u20133); 20 episodes\n|-\n| 2010, 2013\n| ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]''\n| Dr. Gail\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]''\n| Piers Kennedy\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Dragon Age: Redemption]]''\n| Cairn\n| Web series; 6 e