{"title_page": "List of Odia writers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n\n{{unreferenced|date=February 2009}}\n\nThis is a list of notable [[Odia language]] writers from [[Odisha]], [[India]] from the 8th century onward.\n\n== Charyagiti Era of Buddhist poets (7th - 8th Century A.D ) ==\n\n* Kanhupa\n* Luipa\n* [[Saraha|Sarahapada]]\n\n== Pre Sarala Yuga (12th \u2013 14th century A.D) ==\n\n* Raja Balabhadra Bhanja\n* Baccha Das\n* Abhadutta Narayan Swami\n* Markanda Das\n\n==Age of Sarala Yuga (15th Century A.D)==\n\n*[[Sarala Das]] (1465 ? )\n*Arjuna Das\n\n== Panchasakha Era (15th - 16th Century A.D) ==\n\n*[[Atibadi Jagannath Das]] (c. 1491-1550)\n*[[Achyutananda|Achyutananda Das]]\n*Balarama Das\n*Sishu Ananta Das\n*Jasobanta Das\n\n==Age of Upendra Bhanja==\n\n* [[Kabi Samrat Upendra Bhanja]] (C. 1688-1740)\n* [[Kavisurya Baladev Rath]] (c. 1789 \u2013 1845)\n\n==Age of Radhanath==\n\n* [[Fakir Mohan Senapati]]\n* [[Gangadhar Meher]]\n* [[Radhanath Ray]]\n* [[Madhusudan Rao]]\n* [[Nanda Kishore Bal]]\n* [[Reba Ray]]\n\n==Post Colonial Age==\n* [[Gangadhar Meher]]\n* [[Sachidananda Routray]]\n* [[Brajanath Rath]]\n* [[Binod Chandra Nayak]]\n\n==Poetry==\n* [[Brajanath Rath]]\n* [[Ramakanta Rath]]\n* [[Sitakanta Mohapatra]]\n* [[Haraprasad Das]]\n* [[Pratibha Ray]]\n* [[Goutam Jena ]]\n\n==Novelists==\n*[[Krushna Chandra Kar]]\n*[[Gopinath Mohanty]]\n*[[Surendra Mohanty]]\n*[[Manoj Das]]\n*[[Santanu Kumar Acharya]]\n*[[Pratibha Ray]]\n*[[Gourahari Das]]\n\n==Women's Writings and Feminism==\n*[[Sarojini Sahoo]]\n*[[Archana Nayak]]\n*[[Nandini Sahu]]\n\n==Children's literature==\n'''[[Odia language|Odia]] [[children's literature]]''' has a long history. Its roots are in Moukhika Sishu Sahitya, which is a part of the Loka Sahitya meant for the children.  As its development started after modern education was implemented, Odia children's literature is divided in two categories, Odia Moukhika children's literature and Odia written children's literature. \n*[[Ramakrushna Nanda]]\n*[[Krutibas Nayak]]\n*[[Adikanda Mahanta]]\n\n==Drama/Plays==\n*Sesabasantara Chithi(Manoranjan Das\n*Astami Chanda (Purna Chandra Pattanaik)\n\n==Short Story==\n\n*[[Fakir Mohan Senapati]]\n*[[Surendra Mohanty]]\n*[[Manoj Das]]\n*[[Jagadish Mohanty]]\n*[[Sarojini Sahoo]]\n*[[Gourahari Das]]\n*[[Hussain Rabi Gandhi]]\n\n==Popular science==\n*[[Binod Kanungo]]\n*[[Gokulananda Mohapatra]]\n*[[Ramesh Chandra Parida]]\n*[[Kamalakanta Jena]]\n*[[Mayadhar Swain]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Odia Literature]]\n* [[Odia language]]\n* [[Odia people]]\n* [[List of people from Odisha]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100223034947/http://www.sahitya-akademi.gov.in/old_version/awa10315.htm#oriya Sahitya Akademi Award winners in Oriya] ''[[Sahitya Akademi]]''\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100309095153/http://www.riocl.org/ www.riocl.org]\n\n{{inc-lit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odia Writers}}\n[[Category:Odia language|Writers]]\n[[Category:Lists of writers by language]]\n[[Category:Lists of Indian writers]]\n[[Category:Odia-language writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n\n{{unreferenced|date=February 2009}}\n\nThis is a list of notable [[Odia language]] writers from [[Odisha]], [[India]] from the 8th century onward.\n\n== Charyagiti Era of Buddhist poets (7th - 8th Century A.D ) ==\n\n* Kanhupa\n* Luipa\n* [[Saraha|Sarahapada]]\n\n== Pre Sarala Yuga (12th \u2013 14th century A.D) ==\n\n* Raja Balabhadra Bhanja\n* Baccha Das\n* Abhadutta Narayan Swami\n* Markanda Das\n\n==Age of Sarala Yuga (15th Century A.D)==\n\n*[[Sarala Das]] (1465 ? )\n*Arjuna Das\n\n== Panchasakha Era (15th - 16th Century A.D) ==\n\n*[[Atibadi Jagannath Das]] (c. 1491-1550)\n*[[Achyutananda|Achyutananda Das]]\n*Balarama Das\n*Sishu Ananta Das\n*Jasobanta Das\n\n==Age of Upendra Bhanja==\n\n* [[Kabi Samrat Upendra Bhanja]] (C. 1688-1740)\n* [[Kavisurya Baladev Rath]] (c. 1789 \u2013 1845)\n\n==Age 